<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7489500f-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s80105"><num value="80105">§ 80105.</num><heading> Principal office and meetings</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id74895010-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s80105/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Principal Office</inline>.—</heading><content>The principal office of the corporation shall be in the District of Columbia.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id74895011-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s80105/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Meetings</inline>.—</heading><content>The corporation may hold its meetings at places outside the District of Columbia.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id74895012-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7">(<ref href="/us/pl/105/225">Pub. L. 105–225</ref>, <date date="1998-08-12">Aug. 12, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/1360">112 Stat. 1360</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
